The paper discusses machine learning methods, specifically neural nets, and their ability to generalize well from finite labeled data. This suggests that the paper belongs to the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the brittleness of existing neural net approaches, which suggests that it may belong to the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the inability of recurrent sequence-processing nets to stay on track without teacher forcing, which suggests that it may belong to the category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the challenge of achieving robust generalization with adversarial training, which suggests that it may belong to the category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) or Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
